                    The Maintenance Planner shall:

1. Direct PM planning and execution aligned with the Production plan; and coordinate & ensure availability of spare parts, third party & contracted services;

2. Ensure and update PM plans for all equipment and machine, and maintain PM plan catalogue in SAP;

3. Consolidate and review existing PM plans, as needed based on machine and equipment performance, as reported by process owners; and create & enrol PM plan for new equipment;

4. Assist in determining, and provide guide in allocating repairs & maintenance budget;

5. Align with the implementation of policies and standards related but not limited to EHS Hazard Identification & Risk Assessment, Good Manufacturing Practices, ISO 9001:2015 (QMS), HACCP, HALAL, and FSSC; and as in the case may be, form part of the Internal Audit team and ensure compliance on, established management systems mentioned; and

6. Represent the organization, as needed, in functional congregations, especially in liaising with Corporate Maintenance Group, and other Maintenance Planners from different URC BCFG Plants;

7. Perform other tasks and functions as may be delegated by the Immediate Superior.

                    The Maintenance Supervisor shall:

1. Lead and supervise the Maintenance team in executing of electrical & mechanical preventive and/or corrective maintenance of electronics, instrumentation & process control components aligned with production plans and established standards – including but not limited to, process & product quality, machine maintenance, and cost – and contribute to operational compliance based on key performance indicators and key results areas, as aligned with business objectives and business needs;

2. Coordinate with involved department PM plans, basic equipment care, and all corrective or preventive maintenance activities for all electronics, instrumentation & process control components of the line, as needed, based on implemented machine maintenance systems;

3. Ensure implementation of policies and internal memorandum; and align with updates on implemented policies and standards related, but not limited to, EHS Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment, Good Manufacturing Practices, ISO 9001:2015 (QMS), HACCP, HALAL, and FSSC; and as in the case may be, form part of the Internal Audit team and ensure compliance on established management systems mentioned;

4. Conduct daily inspection of the line and ensure compliance to implemented safety and quality systems & standards, as mentioned;

5. Prepare maintenance reports; and lead breakdown analyses, and initiate strategies & action plan to address non-conformances, operational losses, and continuous improvement related to electronics, instrumentation & process control components of the line; and provide guide on electronics, instrumentation & process control maintenance to the assigned team and line & process owners;

6. Align with the implementation of policies and standards related but not limited to EHS Hazard Identification & Risk Assessment, Good Manufacturing Practices, ISO 9001:2015 (QMS), HACCP, HALAL, and FSSC; and as in the case may be, form part of the Internal Audit team and ensure compliance on, established management systems mentioned; and

7. Represent the organization, as needed, in functional congregations, especially in liaising with Corporate Maintenance Group, and other Instrumentation Supervisors from different URC BCFG Plants;

8. Perform assigned tasks for subordinates including, but not limited to, daily direction settings, capability development, talent management, employee discipline, and performance & goals management; and

9. Perform other tasks and functions as may be delegated by the Immediate Superior.

                    II. DUTIES, RESPONSIBILITIES AND AUTHORITIES

The Maintenance Supervisor shall:

1. Execute electrical & mechanical preventive and/or corrective maintenance aligned with production plans and established standards – including but not limited to, process & product quality, and machine maintenance;

2. Coordinate with involved department machine maintenance, basic equipment care, and corrective or preventive maintenance activities for all mechanical and electrical components of the line, as needed, based on implemented machine maintenance systems; and coordinate to the Maintenance Supervisor/s potential non-conformances and possible machine breakdowns;

3. Align with the implementation of policies and standards related but not limited to EHS Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment, Good Manufacturing Practices, ISO 9001:2015 (QMS), HACCP, HALAL, and FSSC; and as in the case may be, form part of the Internal Audit team and ensure compliance on, established management systems mentioned;

4. Conduct daily inspection of the line and ensure compliance to implemented safety and quality systems & standards, as mentioned;

5. Assist in preparing maintenance reports; and participate in breakdown analyses to address non-conformances, operational losses, and continuous improvement related to mechanical and electrical components of the line; and provide feedback on electrical and mechanical maintenance to the assigned team and line & process owners;

6. Accomplish maintenance reports, as needed; and attend turnover activities;

7. Perform other tasks and functions as may be delegated by the Immediate Superior.
